title: Shakeup in state football rankings
text:
Shakeup in state football rankings 
By wbng sports Shakeup in state football rankings September 30, 2015 Updated Sep 30, 2015 at 5:39 PM EDT 
(WBNG Binghamton) Following a blockbuster weekend of high school football games in Section IV, this week's state rankings feature plenty of movement involving local schools. 
Previously top-ranked Tioga dropped from the top spot in Class D to sixth in this week's rankings released by the New York State Sportswriters Association on Wednesday. 
WBNG E-News - Sign Up For Our Newsletter! 
This comes after the Tigers loss to Newark Valley at home last Friday. With the win over Tioga, the Cardinals moved up a spot to ninth in Class C. 
In Class B, Owego drops out of the rankings after Chenango Valley handed the Indians their first loss of the season. 
Meanwhile, Maine-Endwell and Chenango Forks remained ranked No. 1 in their respective classes.
